2000-12-10  Jeffrey Stedfast  <fejj@helixcode.com>
	Beginning of the GMIME_PGP_MIME branch.

	* md5-utils.[c,h]: Added.

	* gmime-exception*: An exception implementation stolen from Camel.

	* pgp-utils.[c,h]: PGP interface code stolen from Spruce and
	Evolution and modified to better handle binary data streams rather
	than only text streams. Also made it so that the program using
	GMime can specify the PGP program at run-time thus making it so
	that there are no build-time dependencies on a PGP program.

	* pgp-mime.[c,h]: A PGP/MIME (rfc2015) implementation using
	pgp-utils and gmime-exception. It goes untested so far but I think
	it should work, though I'd hesitate to say it's a perfect
	implementation.

